  "body": "### Version of Hardhat\n\n2.17.1\n\n### What happened?\n\nHow can I reuse functions in test scripts?\r\n\r\nhere are my files:\r\n----- Sample.js ----\r\n```\r\nconst {some} = require(\"./some.js\");\r\n\r\ndescribe(\"Test1\", function () {\r\n    it(\"Functionality works\", async function () {\r\n\t\tsome.somefunc();\r\n    });\r\n})\r\n```\r\n---- some.js-----\r\n```\r\nconst somefunc = function() {\r\n\tconsole.log(\"works\");\r\n}\r\nmodule.exports = {somefunc};\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhen I run `npx hardhat test` I get \"undefined\" error:\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\n  Test1\r\n    1) Functionality works\r\n\r\n\r\n  0 passing (7ms)\r\n  1 failing\r\n\r\n  1) Test1\r\n       Functionality works:\r\n     TypeError: Cannot read properties of undefined (reading 'somefunc')\r\n      at Context.<anonymous> (Sample.js:6:8)\r\n      at processImmediate (node:internal/timers:466:21)\r\n\r\n```\n\n### Minimal reproduction steps\n\njust run the example\n\n### Search terms\n\n_No response_",
